    "cooking_instructions": [
        {
            "instruction": "<p><strong>Before you begin...</strong></p><p>This recipe takes around 5-10 min to prep, so get your slow cooker and all your ingredients ready, then wash your fruit and veg</p><p>Turn on your <strong>slow cooker </strong>to high</p>",
            "order": 1,
            "image": "/images/instructions/slow-cooker-vietnamese-style-fable-mushroom-and-lemongrass-stew/step-1.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p><strong>Now, let's get started!</strong></p><p>Bash your <strong>lemongrass</strong> with a <strong>rolling pin</strong>, remove the <strong>tough outer layers</strong> of the lemongrass and set aside for later</p><p>Heat a large, wide-based pan (preferable non-stick) over a high heat with a drizzle of <strong>vegetable oil</strong></p><p>Once hot, add your <strong>Fable pulled mushrooms</strong> and<strong> lemongrass inner core[s]</strong> to the dish and cook for 1-2 min or until the mushrooms are lightly browned</p>",
            "order": 2,
            "image": "/images/instructions/slow-cooker-vietnamese-style-fable-mushroom-and-lemongrass-stew/step-2.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Meanwhile, boil half a kettle</p><p>Peel and chop your<strong> brown onion[s]</strong> into wedges</p><p>Crush your <strong>cardamom pod[s]</strong> open by squashing with the side of a knife</p>",
            "order": 3,
            "image": "/images/instructions/slow-cooker-vietnamese-style-fable-mushroom-and-lemongrass-stew/step-3.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Once lightly browned, add the <strong>onion wedges</strong> and <strong>crushed cardamom pod[s]</strong> with 1 tbsp <span class=\"text-purple\">[1 1/2 tbsp] </span><span class=\"text-danger\">[2 tbsp]</span> <strong>flour </strong>and give everything a stir until coated in the flour</p><p>Add your <strong>ginger & garlic paste</strong>, <strong>soy sauce, tamarind paste</strong>, <strong>pho broth paste</strong>, <strong>rice vinegar</strong>, <strong>chilli flakes </strong>(can't handle the heat? Go easy!) with a pinch of <strong>sugar</strong> and 200ml <span class=\"text-purple\">[250ml]</span> <span class=\"text-danger\">[350ml] </span><strong>boiled water</strong></p><p>Stir everything together and bring to the boil</p>",
            "order": 4,
            "image": "/images/instructions/slow-cooker-vietnamese-style-fable-mushroom-and-lemongrass-stew/step-4.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Once boiling, transfer everything from the pan to the <strong>slow cooker</strong></p><p>Give everything a good mix up, then cover and cook on high for 4 hours</p>",
            "order": 5,
            "image": "/images/instructions/slow-cooker-vietnamese-style-fable-mushroom-and-lemongrass-stew/step-5.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Once the stew has 20 min left, add your <strong>basmati rice </strong>and <strong>outer lemongrass layers </strong>with 300ml <span class=\"text-purple\">[390ml]</span> <span class=\"text-danger\">[600ml]</span> <strong>cold water </strong>to a pot with a lid and bring to the boil over a high heat</p><p>Once boiling, reduce the heat to very low and cook, covered, for 10-12 min or until all the water has absorbed and the rice is cooked</p>",
            "order": 6,
            "image": "/images/instructions/slow-cooker-vietnamese-style-fable-mushroom-and-lemongrass-stew/step-6.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Once the rice is done, remove from the heat, add your <strong>sweet pea pods</strong> and put the lid back on for 3 min or until slightly softened</p><p>Once the stew is cooked, discard the<strong> lemongrass core[s]</strong> and <strong>cardamom pod[s]</strong></p>",
            "order": 7,
            "image": "/images/instructions/slow-cooker-vietnamese-style-fable-mushroom-and-lemongrass-stew/step-7.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Serve the<strong> Vietnamese-style Fable mushroom & lemongrass stew</strong>, <strong>fragrant basmati rice </strong>and<strong> sweet pea pods</strong></p><p>Strip your <strong>coriander leaves</strong> from their stalks and scatter over the stew</p><p>Dig in!</p>",
            "order": 8
        }
    ],
